journals.title: Time with Kari
journals.text:
Today and yesterday was the first time I went from home while looking after Kari. I'm going part-time at the university and scared I can't do anything. Usually I feel so disorganised and chaotic. But today and yesterday was the first time I've done it where it's not in the middle of absolute mayhem..
 Well almost, we did have a dispute.... It went pretty good what did we do I put on her raincoat when it rained and we jumped in puddles. We came back inside and we had a shower together which sounds weird I know... But she copied me washing my hair and doing all of that stuff. We did lots of cuddles. She had naps but she wouldn't let me put her down... And then was annoyed when she woke up because I needed to make her food. I've been doing lots of the activities but I haven't been logging them. I keep losing my phone so I need to get to the habit of trying to find a way to keep my phone on me all the time. I did a few activities we made some edible Play-Doh... Kari kept eating it even though it tasted horribly of salt. We did some hand movements and right now she's eating all of my noodles. 

Me and husband are on the brink again. I it's been a good 6 weeks or something. And then a topic came up and we were back to the and we have different views some more same some are not... I need to think about how to make us feel a bit better

mottos.name: Trust Your Gut
mottos.text: If something doesn't feel right, it might not be. Take a step, and listen... maybe make a note somewhere... and see if theres a pattern

mottos.name: Ring Off
mottos.text: You are going to get through this you are going to survive

mottos.name: Goal for this phase
mottos.text: Just live happily. and peacefully. A break for now is what is needed.

mottos.name: No one needs to say anything
mottos.text: We just need to give space to think about it
